## 9. Test Scenarios
The mobile implementation should be considered correct only if these flows work:

1. salesman logs in and loads own profile
2. product list loads with filters
3. product detail loads variants for variant products
4. customer search and create work
5. salesman creates draft with simple products only
6. salesman creates draft with variant products only
7. salesman creates draft with mixed simple and variant products
8. salesman adds multiple variants of the same product in one order
9. draft save recalculates totals without deducting stock
10. draft update works only for own draft
11. confirm succeeds for valid draft and deducts stock once
12. confirm fails with `422` when stock changed after draft save
13. confirmed order becomes read-only
14. salesman cannot edit another salesman’s order
15. salesman can delete own draft
16. salesman cannot delete confirmed order

## 10. Integration Notes
- Mobile should fully adopt the draft-first business and stop using direct create-and-confirm.
- Product detail is the source of truth for variant choice.
- Mobile cart should merge duplicate exact `product + variant` lines before API submission.
- `Save Draft` should remain enabled even with stock warnings.
- `Confirm Order` should be disabled in UI while known stock warnings exist.
- Confirmed-order cancellation flow is not part of this phase.
